checklist.Text: Clear your workbench
Place requested items on workbench
Gather 4M nuclei (2 plates worth)
Resuspend an aliquot of frozen nuclei in 500uL of 0.3M SPBSTM to start
Put samples on ice while counting
Count with the hemocytometer
Count with the ImageXpress Pico
Preheat cyclers to 55 C (lid at 65C) and set to a 5 min cycle, set to “stop” when the lid is heated
Pull out the desired amount of nuclei based on nuclei/uL into a new tube
Set aside the extra (or toss if not needed).
Spin the amount needed (800xg, 5min, 4C).
Remove supernatant.
In a new tube make a master mix of 1.1mL 0.3M SPBSTM and 123.2uL dNTP
Resuspend nuclei in the necessary volume of the buffer/dNTP mix according to how many wells the sample is getting (5uL of mix/well = 20k nuclei/well = 4k nuclei/uL of mix).

Place plates on ice after 5 minute timer is up
Make reaction mix of 140uL water, 560uL 5X Superscript IV buffer and 140uL Superscript IV (200u/ul)

Incubate in Jun's ramp up protocol (2 mins @ 4C, 2mins @ 10C, 2 mins @ 20 C, 2 mins @ 30 C, 2 mins @ 40 C, 2 mins @ 50 C, 15 mins @ 55 C - lid at 65C for all - after hold at 4C) ideally iimmediately place on ice. "Say Check to start timer"
Ice plates until they are cold, around 20 mins. "Say check to start timer"
Place the cool plate on the right side of the liquidator and a pipette box lid with some 0.3 M SPBSTM on the left.
With the liquidator set to 200 uL, pick up and add about 100ul cold 0.3M SPBSTM
Mix in wells, bring back to lid, triturate, pick up some more, wash plate with mixture
Repeat this for 2nd plate into the same lid so that all the RT plates are pooled.
Using a 5 mL pipette (set to 4mL), gather the sample pool and place it into a 40um strainer in a 50mL tube.
Spin 500xg 5min 4C. Pellet will be small but you should be able to see it. "Say check to start timer"
Remove supernatant.
Resuspend in the small residual volume
Wash again with 4mL of 0.3M SPBSTM
Spin at 500xg 5 mins 4C. "Say check to start timer"
Remove supernatant
